    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "75b4061a_bb3f79d0",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLGLSLCodeGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 1010,
      "author": {
        "id": 5640
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-06T16:46:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The \u0027right\u0027 solution is probably to leave the logic here as-is but generate an error in IRGenerator when the layout and modifiers aren\u0027t compatible.\n\nThat said, I generally haven\u0027t really bothered with reporting this class of error, because the generated GLSL will turn out to be invalid and you\u0027ll get an error message from the backend about it anyway. Fixing the error reporting on our end would really just change who ends up reporting the error; certainly not a bad thing to harden our compiler, but I\u0027m also not super stressed about it. Thoughts?",
      "parentUuid": "086420c4_2454f5cb",
      "revId": "f02cdd0b6eeb6abd913ed66f18aa129940f7e717",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
